00:09:08,948 --> 00:09:11,051
- Well, I guess...
- Oh, Ye-eun?

243
00:09:11,518 --> 00:09:13,019
- I guess I can stay.
- How have you been, Ye-eun?

244
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:14,320
- Good. And you?
- That's good.

245
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:16,256
- I'll just stay a little while longer.
- Oh, Ye-eun.

246
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:18,458
- Yes, stay a while longer.
- You look good.

247
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,226
- You look good.
- You don't know her, right?

248
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:21,561
Say hello.

249
00:09:21,628 --> 00:09:25,265
This is Shin Ye-eun,
the marathon club's mascot.

250
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:30,670
Whenever we take a group photo,

251
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:33,473
we put Ye-eun right in the middle.

252
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:36,443
Because she's our club's mascot, you know?

253
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:39,312
- She's so adorable in the middle.
- She's in the center.

254
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:40,780
She's our mascot.

255
00:09:40,847 --> 00:09:44,751
If I'd seen that photo earlier,
I would've stuck around.

256
00:09:44,818 --> 00:09:47,987
- But this is my first time seeing her.
- When did you join the club?

257
00:09:48,054 --> 00:09:49,923
- Around two months ago.
- Oh, really?

258
00:09:49,989 --> 00:09:51,291
- How about you?
- Well...

259
00:09:51,357 --> 00:09:53,226
Maybe 2 or 3 years.

260
00:09:53,293 --> 00:09:54,294
- Right, 2 or 3 years.
- Because...

261
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,329
- So a while.
- she's been busy lately,

262
00:09:56,396 --> 00:09:57,630
- so she couldn't come for a while.
- Right.

263
00:09:57,697 --> 00:09:59,399
- I see.
- She's been busy lately...

264
00:09:59,466 --> 00:10:01,734
- It's been a while, Ye-eun.
- Yes, it has.

265
00:10:01,801 --> 00:10:03,069
You two are close, right?

266
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:04,604
- Yes, we are.
- How have you been?

267
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:06,539
- I've been doing well.
- What have you been doing?

268
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,441
I've been busy.
You know I'm an actress, right?

269
00:10:08,508 --> 00:10:10,176
- We do.
- I've been working.

270
00:10:10,243 --> 00:10:11,211
That must've been tough.

271
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:13,246
- You've been filming?
- It just wrapped up.

272
00:10:13,313 --> 00:10:15,348
- You must've been busy.
- You're done now? Good for you.

273
00:10:15,415 --> 00:10:16,916
You posted on Instagram
that you went to Germany.

274
00:10:16,983 --> 00:10:18,351
- Oh, that's right!
- Really?

275
00:10:18,418 --> 00:10:19,586
You saw what I posted on Instagram?

276
00:10:19,652 --> 00:10:20,653
Of course I did.

277
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,155
- As your fan, I've also been
- Hey.

278
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:24,023
- lurking in your account too.
- Really? You're lying.

279
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:24,958
I'm not.

280
00:10:25,024 --> 00:10:27,961
- Really? Then let's follow each other.
- Okay.

281
00:10:28,528 --> 00:10:29,629
- Seriously?
- Yes.

282
00:10:29,729 --> 00:10:31,464
I've been following more people lately.

283
00:10:31,531 --> 00:10:32,432
- You have?
- Really?

284
00:10:32,499 --> 00:10:35,168
Send me a request.
I'll think about accepting it.

285
00:10:36,269 --> 00:10:37,403
Where in Germany were you?

286
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,172
I was in a city called Heidelberg.

287
00:10:39,706 --> 00:10:41,341
- That sounds delicious.
- Right.

288
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:43,276
- They have lots of good food.
- Did you try Schweinshaxe?

289
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:45,211
- I did.
- What about draft beer?

290
00:10:45,278 --> 00:10:46,179
The non-alcoholic version.

291
00:10:46,246 --> 00:10:47,947
- Oh, I see.
- I can't drink alcohol.

292
00:10:48,014 --> 00:10:49,482
You can't even drink beer?

293
00:10:49,549 --> 00:10:50,517
I don't like it.

294
00:10:50,583 --> 00:10:53,453
- But Germany is famous for beer.
- Yes, I heard that too.

295
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,556
But our fried chicken is more delicious
than Schweinshaxe, right?

296
00:10:56,623 --> 00:10:57,790
- Absolutely!
- Of course.

297
00:10:57,857 --> 00:10:59,559
- I haven't eaten yet.
- Let's eat, then!

298
00:10:59,626 --> 00:11:01,194
- Let's eat.
- I got everything ready.

299
00:11:01,261 --> 00:11:03,863
Min is really good
at cooking fried chicken.

300
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:06,566
Don't overwork yourself, Min.
And be careful of the oil.

301
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,101
- By the way, Won-hun...
- It's hot.

302
00:11:08,601 --> 00:11:11,371
- All right, now. It all looks so good.
- Here you go.

303
00:11:11,437 --> 00:11:14,174
We have the best sister ever.

304
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,942
- Look at that.
- Ye-eun hasn't eaten yet.

305
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:17,777
- Help yourself.
- Please do.

306
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:19,913
- Let's make a toast.
- Let's do that.

307
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,147
Fill up your glasses.

308
00:11:21,214 --> 00:11:22,882
When I say "Running Crew," you say "run."

309
00:11:22,949 --> 00:11:25,618
- Running Crew!
- Run!

310
00:11:28,488 --> 00:11:29,889
Help yourself.

311
00:11:29,956 --> 00:11:31,858
- Yes, you should eat while it's hot.
- Can we?

312
00:11:31,925 --> 00:11:33,693
- Here you go.
- Eat up, Ye-eun.

313
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,328
- Thank you.
- Do you want a chicken wing?

314
00:11:35,795 --> 00:11:38,164
This fried chicken is amazing.

315
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,335
Here's a chicken wing. Eat up.

316
00:11:42,402 --> 00:11:43,570
- It's good, right?
- Yes.

317
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:46,506
- Wait, so...
- It's crunchy.

318
00:11:46,573 --> 00:11:48,241
- It's warm.
- It came out this morning.

319
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:50,843
You're getting better and better
at frying chicken, Min.

320
00:11:51,477 --> 00:11:52,845
I'm serious.

321
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:55,248
- Why do you never answer me?
- Are you not close?

322
00:11:55,315 --> 00:11:57,283
No, we're close.
She just doesn't talk to me.

323
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:01,754
What's your PR, Ye-eun?

324
00:12:01,821 --> 00:12:02,789
- Personal record?
- PR?

325
00:12:03,122 --> 00:12:04,424
Let me do my PR.

326
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,726
Hello, I'm Kim Won-hun.

327
00:12:06,793 --> 00:12:08,461
I like to exercise,

328
00:12:08,528 --> 00:12:09,729
and I have a YouTube channel.

329
00:12:09,796 --> 00:12:11,898
I have 38... I mean 380,000 subscribers...

330
00:12:12,198 --> 00:12:14,067
He can't even pronounce it.

331
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:16,836
- You can't even do it properly.
- It's not a lot of subscribers.

332
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:19,205
- You can't even say it properly.
- Doing PR like this

333
00:12:19,272 --> 00:12:21,975
in front of so many people
is a little awkward for me.

334
00:12:22,041 --> 00:12:23,109
So Ye-eun,

335
00:12:23,176 --> 00:12:26,279
did you imagine a real-life comedian
could be so unfunny?

336
00:12:27,347 --> 00:12:28,381
- Unbelievable, right?
- Well,

337
00:12:28,448 --> 00:12:29,482
- it's not all to me.
- He's funny, though.

338
00:12:29,549 --> 00:12:30,717
Not all comedians are good.

339
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:31,951
I thought he was good.

340
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:34,621
You're stabbing me in the back
with a smile!

341
00:12:36,389 --> 00:12:41,427
Aren't you too busy
to run a marathon with us, though?

342
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:43,763
Actually, I'm not running a marathon.

343
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:50,637
The truth is, I've been staying away
because I don't want to run a marathon.

344
00:12:50,703 --> 00:12:52,171
Why not?

345
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:53,673
Why don't you want to?

346
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:55,074
You're not going to run at all?

347
00:12:55,141 --> 00:12:57,543
That's right. Running is too hard for me.

348
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:59,479
Is it that you don't feel strong enough?

349
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:00,713
What don't you like about it?

350
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,115
Running a marathon

351
00:13:02,181 --> 00:13:04,350
makes my legs swell up so much

352
00:13:04,417 --> 00:13:05,752
and my heart beat too fast.

353
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:07,520
My skin gets saggy too.

354
00:13:07,587 --> 00:13:08,921
Your skin gets saggy?

355
00:13:08,988 --> 00:13:11,724
Wait a minute.
You say you won't run a marathon with us,

356
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:14,594
- but you ran one with Sean, didn't you?
- Yes, that's true.

357
00:13:14,661 --> 00:13:17,664
- You ran one with Sean, didn't you?
- Yes, that's true.

358
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:19,265
- What's up with that?
- What?

359
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:22,502
Well, I first started
running a marathon by myself

360
00:13:22,935 --> 00:13:24,671
to lose some weight.

361
00:13:24,737 --> 00:13:26,706
Then I found out
Sean does a lot of volunteer work.

362
00:13:26,773 --> 00:13:27,640
- He does.
- Right.

363
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:31,210
So I reached out to him
to see if I could join him.

364
00:13:31,277 --> 00:13:36,349
But he misunderstood and thought
I wanted to run a marathon with him.

365
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:39,686
So I ended up running a whole marathon.

366
00:13:39,752 --> 00:13:42,155
How long did you train for?

367
00:13:42,221 --> 00:13:44,824
The training started every day at 6 a.m.

368
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:46,659
Wasn't it incredibly hard

369
00:13:46,726 --> 00:13:49,495
to match Sean's pace as a novice?

370
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:51,464
- I couldn't match it.
- You couldn't keep up.

371
00:13:51,531 --> 00:13:52,432
It's impossible.

372
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,267
- He runs 1km in 3 minutes.
- It's really hard.

373
00:13:54,334 --> 00:13:55,768
- Run 1km in 3 minutes?
- Are you serious?

374
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,270
- He's like a pro.
- He's really good.

375
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:58,671
That's basically a professional runner.

376
00:13:58,738 --> 00:14:00,340
- Exactly.
- I fell behind so many times.

377
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:02,909
I'd be like, "Please, go on without me."

378
00:14:02,975 --> 00:14:04,644
- Even at the actual race...
- Yes?

379
00:14:04,711 --> 00:14:07,280
- You know that goal line?
- The finishing line?

380
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:09,015
Everyone crossed it so triumphantly,

381
00:14:09,082 --> 00:14:10,683
but I just said to myself, "Never again."

382
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:13,219
- No sense of triumph at all?
- None. It was so hard.

383
00:14:13,286 --> 00:14:14,420
Instead of celebrating,

384
00:14:14,487 --> 00:14:16,489
- you were cursing under your breath.
- Yes, exactly.

385
00:14:16,556 --> 00:14:18,624
But then did you see Sean going like...

386
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:19,826
"Ye-eun!

387
00:14:20,593 --> 00:14:22,729
- Come on, Ye-eun. Let's go."
- Don't do it.

388
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:24,464
"I'm waiting for you."

389
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:27,533
"I'm running past your house today,
Ye-eun. Will you join me?"

390
00:14:28,501 --> 00:14:30,236
- "I'll wait for you."
- He does reach out to me sometimes,

391
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:32,438
but I don't have the courage to
actually join him.

392
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:34,540
- He says he'll wait for you.
- I can't do that again.

393
00:14:34,607 --> 00:14:37,143
Why don't you send
a video message to Sean?

394
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:39,512
Hello, Sean. The truth is...

395
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:44,550
I wasn't that busy.
I just didn't want to run anymore.

396
00:14:45,151 --> 00:14:46,753
- So adorable.
- So adorable.

397
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:48,554
- Why are you so cute?
- So cute.

398
00:14:48,621 --> 00:14:51,157
I still want to do some volunteer work,

399
00:14:51,224 --> 00:14:54,327
but I don't want to run.

400
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:56,429
- So cute.
- You sound so sincere.

401
00:14:56,496 --> 00:14:58,164
- He'll understand.
- Of course.

402
00:14:58,231 --> 00:14:59,532
Let her go, Sean.

403
00:14:59,599 --> 00:15:00,833
I'll send Ji Ye-eun your way instead.

404
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,034
Behave yourself!

405
00:15:02,602 --> 00:15:05,071
You're so adorable.

406
00:15:05,138 --> 00:15:07,707
So you're starring in a new TV show.
Who else will be on it?

407
00:15:07,774 --> 00:15:10,676
Oh, Lee Jae-wook is the other lead.

408
00:15:11,878 --> 00:15:13,379
People say I look like him.

409
00:15:13,446 --> 00:15:14,313
You goddamn liar!

410
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:16,048
People say I look like him.

411
00:15:16,115 --> 00:15:17,283
You goddamn liar!

412
00:15:17,984 --> 00:15:19,719
- You crossed a line.
- You went too far.

413
00:15:19,786 --> 00:15:21,254
- That's too much.
- What's wrong with him?

414
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:24,791
It's true, though.
I've actually heard people say that.

415
00:15:24,857 --> 00:15:26,626
- I even met him in person.
- What do you think?

416
00:15:26,692 --> 00:15:29,195
Does Won-hun
look like Lee Jae-wook at all?

417
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:32,298
She thinks it's a load of crap.

418
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:33,399
Just say it out loud.

419
00:15:33,466 --> 00:15:34,867
- Everyone just clams up.
- Trying to be polite.

420
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,404
Tell him it's a load of crap.

421
00:15:38,905 --> 00:15:40,306
It's a load...

422
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:43,075
- She's too nice to say it.
- Oh no.

423
00:15:43,142 --> 00:15:44,477
It's a load of crap.

424
00:15:44,544 --> 00:15:46,045
So cute!

425
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:47,980
- That was a joke, right?
- You're so cute.

426
00:15:48,047 --> 00:15:50,583
- I didn't know you were this hilarious.
- So cute.

427
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:52,084
- I'm sorry.
- So what's the show?

428
00:15:52,151 --> 00:15:54,454
- What's it about?
- It's a medical drama.

429
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:55,621
A medical drama?

430
00:15:55,688 --> 00:15:58,558
Lee Jae-wook plays a public health doctor,

431
00:15:58,624 --> 00:15:59,926
which means he's in the military--

432
00:15:59,992 --> 00:16:01,360
- Did you say "pockmarked"?
- "Public health."

433
00:16:01,427 --> 00:16:02,762
- Did you say "pockmarked"?
- "Public health."

434
00:16:02,829 --> 00:16:03,863
Public health doctor.

435
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:05,731
- He thought you said "pockmarked"
- I thought...

436
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,500
- and looked so startled for a second.
- So it's an actual thing?

437
00:16:07,934 --> 00:16:10,136
Am I everyone's punching bag today?

438
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:12,071
- Is that it?
- Public health doctor?

439
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:14,040
- Then what about you?
- I play a nurse.

440
00:16:14,106 --> 00:16:16,142
- Oh, it suits you.
- It suits you so well.

441
00:16:16,209 --> 00:16:17,610
- It's a perfect role for you.
- Yes.

442
00:16:17,677 --> 00:16:18,678
Not a villain, right?

443
00:16:18,744 --> 00:16:19,912
No.

444
00:16:20,213 --> 00:16:22,114
I still remember Ye-eun as...

445
00:16:22,181 --> 00:16:23,983
What was the character's name? Yeon...

446
00:16:24,050 --> 00:16:25,751
- Yeon-jin.
- That's right.

447
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:27,653
When I was watching Yeon-jin
on the screen,

448
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:30,056
I just wanted to punch her

449
00:16:30,122 --> 00:16:32,692
if I ever met her in person.

450
00:16:32,758 --> 00:16:34,093
Your acting was so good.

451
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,695
- She was phenomenal.
- I remember.

452
00:16:35,761 --> 00:16:37,830
You were a total jerk back then.

453
00:16:39,298 --> 00:16:41,634
- A complete jerk.
- Did some people give you a hard time?

454
00:16:41,968 --> 00:16:44,337
Do you have to emphasize it like that?

455
00:16:45,037 --> 00:16:47,106
When you're playing a villain,

456
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:50,276
does it affect you negatively in any way?

457
00:16:51,544 --> 00:16:53,746
I was working on both <i>The Glory</i>
and <i>Revenge of Others</i>

458
00:16:53,813 --> 00:16:55,381
- at the same time,
- Filming at the same time.

459
00:16:55,448 --> 00:16:58,217
and they were
both dark and serious titles.

460
00:16:58,718 --> 00:17:01,654
It certainly affected my mood
and made me more melancholy.

461
00:17:01,721 --> 00:17:03,456
- Oh, for real?
- That makes sense.

462
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:06,526
You know how you become happier
if you tell yourself you're happy?

463
00:17:06,592 --> 00:17:09,262
- The opposite works in the same way.
- Really?

464
00:17:09,328 --> 00:17:12,064
It must've been tough
to work on both at the same time.

465
00:17:12,131 --> 00:17:13,132
- Yes, it must've been.
- Right.

466
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:14,901
- Yes, but... I was fine.
- You're fine?

467
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,769
But aren't there people like Sun-i

468
00:17:16,836 --> 00:17:19,005
- who think you're villainous in real life
- Right.

469
00:17:19,071 --> 00:17:21,240
even though you're so bright and innocent,

470
00:17:21,307 --> 00:17:23,042
- Right.
- and insult you when they see you?

471
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:25,745
- I'm sure something like that's happened.
- It has.

472
00:17:25,811 --> 00:17:27,280
- Has it happened before?
- Not necessarily by older people.

473
00:17:27,346 --> 00:17:28,948
But it actually makes me happier

474
00:17:29,015 --> 00:17:30,349
- Since you were convincing?
- because it means I did well.

475
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:31,350
What if an elderly lady says,

476
00:17:31,417 --> 00:17:33,819
"There goes that damn bully Yeon-jin"?

477
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:34,787
I'd actually like it.

478
00:17:34,854 --> 00:17:36,956
If not older people,
then who said that to you?

479
00:17:37,023 --> 00:17:39,892
Maybe someone who's meeting me
for the first time

480
00:17:39,959 --> 00:17:42,495
would assume I'm a bit intense.
Something like that.

481
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:43,496
- It affected your first impression?
- First impression.

482
00:17:43,563 --> 00:17:45,231
